        "content": "<p>To finish off the thread I tried to generalize this into a proposition which is true when a function from <code>R</code> to <code>R</code> has a vertical/horizontal asymptote:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">vertical_asymptote</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_top</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ¨</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ aâº of f is âˆ</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_bot</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ¨</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ aâº of f is -âˆ</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_top</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ¨</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ aâ» of f is âˆ</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_bot</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ aâ» of f is -âˆ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">horizontal_asymptote</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_top</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ¨</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ âˆ of f is a</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">filter.tendsto</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">filter.at_bot</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ -âˆ of f is a</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
